"{\"recipe\":\"Chocolate Mars Bar Rice Krispie Treats</br></br>Ingredients:</br>- 2 Mars Bars</br>- 2 tablespoons of butter</br>- 2 cups of Rice Krispies</br></br>Instructions:</br></br>1. In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat.</br></br>2. Once melted, add the Mars Bars and stir until completely melted.</br></br>3. Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the Rice Krispies until evenly coated.</br></br>4. Transfer the mixture to an 8x8 inch baking dish lined with parchment paper.</br></br>5. Press the mixture down firmly into the pan.</br></br>6. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until set.</br></br>7. Cut into bars and enjoy!\"}"